  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Now that we are moving into the Ruby release, it is important that we think about how sync would work for shard chains. A lot of work has been put into Geth's fast sync by using a checkpoints/skeleton strategy to rapidly download chaindata via peer to peer.\r\n\r\nThis will be more of an open discussion where we think about where the sync code should go in our implementation and how in-depth we should go into this for the ruby release.\r\n",
