    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Based on the [Sharding P2P Design](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1cthKuGPreOSQH96Ujt7sArcT-IRICk6b-QcdD0EnLsI/edit#heading=h.4d4hnezaletr) created by @prestonvanloon, we can design a basic sync structure that responds to messages from a specific peer only based on the Shardchain Sync design doc created [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1Z9ORAX5heRn8_9cZyZjDNgOH-mBQxgQcRqmlHwfZiUE/edit#heading=h.4d4hnezaletr). \r\n\r\nGiven that specifics of underlying p2p mechanisms have not been defined yet, we can still use Go's interfaces to create a system we can mock with fixtures or other test data to unblock development. I will be taking on the lead with a PR for this idea. @prestonvanloon @nisdas @terenc3t ",
